content: Wow, when you take pause as a reporter and just be. Today I was outside of the ER at Jamaica Hospital. I watched family members who lost loved one in that fire in #queens scream, cry, hug and ask WHY! A few young men just couldn't find words, clearly could not get their heads around what happened and just sobbed. One young man collapsed in a friend's arms. Another, looked for comfort, some kind of answers from other relatives. Awkward, upsetting, it was agonizing seeing folks at the worst possible minutes of their lives. You remain respectable, do not interrupt them as their world literally crumbles around them. 5 people, 3 kids, were killed in a matter of minutes. This family's course in this universe has violently, coldly, unfairly been altered. Tonight I say a little prayer for this family,  #abc7ny

content: What a week! So strange and fascinating this life I live. Mother's Day I, for a brief few hours, I stepped  into someone else's nightmare. A mom on #longisland pushed her daughter out of the way of s speeding car. Mom was killed but saved her only daughter. Met an amazing couple in #coneyisland , stray bullet pierced their bedroom window but incredibly they were not hurt. I worked with a true legend in the entertainment work @sirjohnofficial So cool, does makeup for some of the most gorgeous women in the world, #beyonce . Had the honor of meeting legends, #lyndacarter #marlothomas #reginaking #lynnwhitfield. Then today spoke to a mom and daughter nearly killed in #timessquare . Both hit by that speeding car. It's my Friday, taking a break, quiet time with niece and nephew on the couch. It's the simple things . And yes, I'm ok ❤️#abc7ny #NYC
